title: HPI Spencer
content: The patient reports pain in her left index finger for a few months, which has worsened and not improved. She is seeking an injection at this visit.

title: Musculoskeletal
content: left upper extremity skin is clean, dry, and tacky without erythema. Acute moderate tenderness on left index finger with an A1 polii. There is walking catching. There is triggering on index finger. Excellent range of motion overall. Able to give a thumbs up, et cetera, et cetera.

title: Imaging Results
content: X-rays of the finger are normal.

title: Plan
content: Trigger injection will be performed today.
